    "image_with_text_t6KzFw": {
      "type": "image-with-text",
      "blocks": {
        "text_CcwiLn": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p><a href=\"https://studiofundamentals.com/\">Studio Fundamentals</a> is a pottery studio located at 510 Clark Drive in East Vancouver. Founded in 2017 by May Ann Villanueva, a Filipino immigrant with a background in communication design, the studio stems from her desire to live creatively, share skills, and foster a bonded community.</p><p>Vancouver-based ceramicist May Ann is reshaping the face of ceramics in her community. With the creation of Studio Fundamentals, she is developing a space that offers accessibility for BIPOC individuals to practice the art of pottery. As a self-taught artist, she embraces cultural and social challenges while championing positive change around her.</p><p>We spent the morning with May Ann at her studio to learn more about the vision behind Studio Fundamentals and witness her students at work, honing their craft.</p>",
            "text_style": "body"
          }
        }
      },
