    "image_with_text_NjQ3EM": {
      "type": "image-with-text",
      "blocks": {
        "text_ENV8fL": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<h3>Q:  What’s your advice for someone looking to get into pottery?</h3><p>A: Take classes, whether at a community centre or any pottery studio. My biggest advice for learning anything creative is to really just stick with it. You might feel lost or think it’s not for you, but perseverance and commitment are key. Always pat yourself on the back for any small achievements you make, as they help push you forward to keep going.</p><h3>Q:  Where do you go when you are looking for inspiration?</h3><p>A: I like to step outside the mindset of a potter. I focus on calming my mind and finding ease. Whether it’s climbing outdoors, visiting another city, or stepping outside my comfort zone, I seek inspiration from everything in life—not just art.</p>",
            "text_style": "body"
          }
        }
      },
      "block_order": [
        "text_ENV8fL"
      ],
      "settings": {
        "image": "shopify://shop_images/MAY_ANN_4X5-7090.jpg",
